[size=3][b]Requirements[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/19]Darktide Mod Loader[/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/8]Darktide Mod Framework (DMF)[/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/176]Solo Play[/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/183]Tertium 5[/url] or [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/725]Tertium 6[/url] — optional. BetterBots v0.8.0+ has built-in class profiles with talents and blessed weapons. Tertium is still useful if you want bots to use your own player characters.
[/list]

[b]Note:[/b] Tertium 5 can crash on startup with newer classes (Arbites, Hive Scum). If this happens, use [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/725]Tertium 6[/url] instead — it supports all 6 classes.

[size=3][b]Install[/b][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Extract [font=Courier New]BetterBots.zip[/font] into your Darktide [font=Courier New]mods/[/font] folder
[*]Add [font=Courier New]BetterBots[/font] to [font=Courier New]mods/mod_load_order.txt[/font] (below [font=Courier New]dmf[/font])
[*]Re-patch mods
[/list]

[size=3][b]Verify[/b][/size]

Look for [font=Courier New]BetterBots loaded[/font] and [font=Courier New]injected meta_data for ...[/font] in game chat on mission start.

[size=3][b]Known issues[/b][/size]

[b]Known bugs:[/b]
[list]
[/list]

[b]Vanilla bot limitations being addressed:[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Objective-aware abilities[/b] — bots don't yet adjust ability usage to protect allies interacting with objectives. ([url=https://github.com/hummat/BetterBots/issues/37]#37[/url])
[/list]

[b]Other limitations:[/b]
[list]
[*]Item-based abilities use a heuristic wield/use/unwield sequence — new or changed weapon templates may not be recognized
[*]Mods are disabled after every Darktide update — re-patch required
[*]Hive Scum abilities (Enhanced Desperado, Rampage, Stimm Field) are untested — DLC required for validation
[*]Bot mastiff names may appear to the player despite the "mine only" companion name setting — this is a vanilla issue with how bots share network identity
[/list]

